<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> rdfs:label "Secondary Source: Broughton MRR I" ;
	a dprr:SecondarySource ;
	dprr:hasName "The Magistrates of the Roman Republic, Vol. I" ;
	dprr:hasBiblio "Broughton, T. R. S., The Magistrates of the Roman Republic, Vol. I. Published by the American Philological Association. New York 1952." ;
	dprr:hasAbbreviation "Broughton MRR I" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8063> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8063" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Praef. soc.? 109. Plutarch (Mar. 8.1-2; see MRR 1.547) refers to him as a praefectus fabrum (#).\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3473> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3473" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Commander and sole survivor of the troops at Vaga, and so was convicted of treason and put to death (Sall. Iug. 68-69; Plut. Mar. 8.1-2; App. Num. 3)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3472> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3472" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "According to Appian (Num. 3), Turpilius was a Roman. Could Mommsen's text of Sall. Iug. 69.4 (Nam is civis ex Latio erat), if correct, mean that he was a Roman citizen of Latin origin ? See Reid, JRS 1 (1911) 77-83, and Sherwin-White, Rom. Citizenship 127f., on the status of Turpilius; and on the date of the massacre at Vaga, Carcopino, RH 158 (1928) 17f." .
